Ahead of the 2023 general election, the United Nations Electoral Assistance Division (UNEAD) in Nigeria has met with the leadership of the All Progressives Congress (APC) to seek a peaceful and inclusiveness in the forthcoming election. The UNEAD made the call on Wednesday after a meeting with the APC National Secretary, Sen. Iyiola Omisore, representing the National Chairman, Sen. Abdullahi Adamu, at the party’s national secretariat in Abuja. The Electoral Division delegation, led by Serge Kubwimana, said they were at the APC headquarters to express their intent to contribute to a peaceful and inclusive process next year. According to Kubwimana who was accompanied by the APC National Publicity Secretary, Barr Felix Morka, Director of Organisation, Prof. Ussiju Medaner and other members said, “The country has strong institutions and the ability to run its elections. “There are issues of course, but Nigeria is not the only place where you see issues around elections. So our role again here is to see how we can support one of our member states.” “We have conferred with the APC National Secretary on behalf of the National Chairman, We have done the same with INEC, government, civil society organizations, major political parties, faith-based organizations, and inter-party advisory council to name a few. “We are here to express our intent to contribute to a peaceful and inclusive process next year and to see where we can be of value.”